Channel Ray			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Channel Energy																									PRETEXT:Channel energy class feature.																				DESC:You can focus your channeled energy on a single target.											SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:When you channel energy, you can project a ray from your holy symbol instead of creating a burst. You must succeed at a ranged touch attack to hit an unwilling target; your target is then affected by the channeled energy as normal and receives a saving throw. Willing creatures need no attack roll. The ray has a range of 30 feet per channel energy die, and its save DC is increased by 2.
Clinging Climber		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																														PRESKILL:1,Climb=3	PRESTAT:1,STR=13	PRETEXT:Str 13, Climb 3 ranks.																					DESC:Using leverage and pure brawn, you can cling to a cliff, rope, or ladder with your legs to free both of your hands.	SOURCEPAGE:p.14	BENEFIT:As a move action while climbing, you can cling to your climbing surface with your legs by succeeding at a Climb check (DC = the DC to climb the surface). If successful, you can make attacks with a two-handed ranged weapon and reload ranged weapons until you resume climbing. The GM may rule that this feat doesn't work on certain climbing surfaces.
Combat Advice		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																														DESC:Your succinct words can aid an ally even in the heat of battle.										SOURCEPAGE:p.14	BENEFIT:As a move action, you can offer useful advice to an ally engaged in combat at just the right moment. Designate an enemy; your ally gains a +2 competence bonus on her next attack roll against that enemy. You must be able to clearly see your ally and the designated enemy, and your ally must be able to hear you.
Concentrated Splash	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Precise Shot,Throw Anything																									PRETEXT:Precise Shot or Throw Anything.																				DESC:You can limit the splatter of your splash weapons to increase damage against your target.						SOURCEPAGE:p.6	BENEFIT:When you deal a direct hit to a creature with a weapon that normally deals splash damage, you can choose to forgo dealing splash damage. If you do, the damage dealt to the target of the direct hit increases by 50%%. This damage is multiplied on a critical hit.
Covering Fire		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot																											PRETEXT:Point-Blank Shot.																						DESC:You distract your enemies with ranged attacks to protect your allies.									SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:You can use the aid another action with a ranged attack against an opponent, regardless of whether they threaten an ally. Range penalties apply to this attack roll. Choose one ally when making the attack. If the attack is successful, that ally gains a +2 bonus to AC against that opponent's next attack, as long as it comes before the beginning of your next turn. All allies with this feat also gain this bonus against that opponent.
Directed Disarm		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Disarm,Greater Disarm		PREMULT:1,[PRESTAT:1,INT=13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13]									PRETEXT:Int 13, Combat Expertise, Greater Disarm, Improved Disarm, base attack bonus +11.									PRETOTALAB:11	DESC:A weapon you pull from one enemy's grip flies toward another enemy.									SOURCEPAGE:p.6	BENEFIT:When you successfully disarm an opponent, the disarmed weapon lands up to 15 feet away from its wielder, in the direction you choose. You can make a ranged attack as an immediate action with the disarmed weapon against another opponent, if the disarmed weapon is light or one-handed. If not a thrown weapon, you take a –4 penalty on the attack roll. You take a –4 penalty on your attack roll if you do not have a free hand.
Distant Spell Link	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot,Far Shot	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Animal Companion,TYPE.Special Mount,TYPE.Familiar,TYPE.Eidolon								PRETEXT:Enlarge Spell or Reach SpellAPG; animal companion, eidolon, familiar, or other allied creature with the share spells ability.				DESC:You can share spells and grant touch spells to your companion creature over a great distance.					SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:The range of your allied creature's share spells ability increases to close (%1 feet) as long as you have line of effect to the creature when you cast the shared spell. This ability works with the deliver touch spells ability, as well.|25+(floor(CASTERLEVEL/2)*5)
Exceptional Pull		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deadly Aim								PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]								PRETEXT:Dex 13, Deadly Aim, base attack bonus +3.															PRETOTALAB:3	DESC:You have mastered techniques to get the most out of composite bows.									SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:When you wield a ranged weapon that you are proficient with and that has a strength rating, add 2 to the weapon's strength rating. You don't take a penalty on attack rolls for having a Strength modifier lower than the strength rating of a weapon, provided you're proficient with that weapon.
Expansive Trap Ability	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																				PRETEXT:Ability to use ranger traps (UM p.64) or land mines (Dungeoneer's Handbook p.23).												DESC:Your ranger traps and land mines occupy a larger area.												SOURCEPAGE:p.14	BENEFIT:You can designate any ranger trap or land mine you lay to occupy up to 4 contiguous squares of your choice. When the trap is activated, the effect is centered on whichever square the triggering creature first entered. If more than one square is entered simultaneously, choose at random.
Friendly Fire Maneuvers	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot,Precise Shot																									PRETEXT:Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot.																				DESC:You and your teammates can anticipate one another's ranged attacks and stay out of each others' way.				SOURCEPAGE:p.14	BENEFIT:Allies who also have this feat cannot provide soft cover to enemies, allowing you to make attacks of opportunity against an enemy even if those allies grant you soft cover against that foe's attacks. If an ally who also has this feat casts a spell that targets the area you are in and it allows a Reflex saving throw to avoid the effect, you gain a +4 dodge bonus on that saving throw.
Lie Low			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																														DESC:You're even harder to see when prone than most are.												SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:If you have been prone since the end of your last turn, the penalty on Perception checks for others to notice you increases by 1 for every 20 feet between you and the observer, to a maximum increase of 5 at 100 feet. This stacks with the normal modifier for distance.
Lob Shot			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot,Far Shot																										PRETEXT:Far Shot, Point-Blank Shot.																					DESC:You can make a high, arcing shot to strike your opponents from above.									SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:While making a ranged attack, you can ignore any cover bonuses to AC, including total cover, unless the target also has cover from above, such as a roof or forest canopy. When using this feat, treat your target as if it were one range increment farther away. You can't use this feat unless you have headroom equal to at least half the attack's range.
Proxy Summoning		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																				PRETEXT:Ability to cast conjuration (summoning) spells or a conjuration (summoning) spell-like ability, caster level 5th.						DESC:Creatures you summon can act as proxies to deliver your spells to foes.									SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:Whenever you cast a touch spell while adjacent to a creature you summoned (including an eidolon), you can have the summoned creature carry the spell's charge. Once the spell is cast, you and any creature you summon gain the share spells ability (CRB p.52).
Ranged Disarm		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Targeting	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deadly Aim								PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]								PRETEXT:Dex 13, Deadly Aim, base attack bonus +1.															PRETOTALAB:1	DESC:A well-placed shot disarms your foe.															SOURCEPAGE:p.8	BENEFIT:As a full-round action, you can attempt to perform a disarm combat maneuver with a ranged weapon at a –2 penalty. Add your Dexterity modifier to your CMB in place of your Strength modifier and apply range penalties to your combat maneuver check, doubling the penalties from range increments. If your target is more than 30 feet away, you take an additional –2 penalty. If the disarm attempt is successful, the target also takes damage as if you had made a successful attack with that weapon. You cannot be disarmed by failing this disarm attempt.
Ranged Trip			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Targeting	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deadly Aim								PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]								PRETEXT:Dex 13, Deadly Aim, base attack bonus +1.															PRETOTALAB:1	DESC:A shot to the leg causes your foe to fall prone.													SOURCEPAGE:p.9	BENEFIT:As a full-round action, you can attempt to perform a trip combat maneuver with a ranged weapon at a –2 penalty. Add your Dexterity modifier to your CMB in place of your Strength modifier and apply range penalties to your combat maneuver check, doubling the penalties from range increments. If your target is more than 30 feet away, you take an additional –2 penalty. If the trip attempt is successful, the target also takes damage as if you had made a successful attack with that weapon. You can't be knocked prone by failing the trip attempt.
Relentless Shot		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot																											PRETEXT:Point-Blank Shot, base attack bonus +6.																PRETOTALAB:6	DESC:You keep your aim steady on a downed foe.														SOURCEPAGE:p.7	BENEFIT:When you trip an opponent within 30 feet with a ranged attack, you threaten that opponent until your next turn. You can make attacks of opportunity against that opponent with ranged weapons. This effect ends if you attack another target or the opponent moves from its current square.
Seeking Spell		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Metamagic																																																														DESC:You can cast spells that bend around barriers to reach their intended destination.							SOURCEPAGE:p.13	BENEFIT:A seeking spell's range can bend around obstacles to reach the intended target. You can define the route yourself or unambiguously identify a target and allow the spell to determine its own path. A ranged attack roll made to deliver a seeking spell is not subject to cover or concealment. A seeking spell uses up a spell slot 2 levels higher than the spell's actual level.
Throw Back Arrows		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deflect Arrows,Improved Unarmed Strike,Snatch Arrows	PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,17],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,17]								PRETEXT:Dex 17, Deflect Arrows, Improved Unarmed Strike, Snatch Arrows.															DESC:When you catch arrows and other ranged ammunition, you can immediately hurl them at your enemies.				SOURCEPAGE:p.9	BENEFIT:When using the Snatch Arrows feat, you can throw a caught piece of ranged ammunition (but not a firearm bullet) as though it were a thrown weapon with a range increment of 20 feet (even though it isn't your turn). The thrown ammunition deals the normal amount of damage for its type plus your Strength modifier, and you don't take a penalty for throwing a weapon that isn't designed to be thrown. This attack provokes attacks of opportunity as normal. You must have at least one hand free (holding nothing) to use this feat.
Trick Shooter		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deadly Aim								PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]								PRETEXT:Dex 13, Deadly Aim, base attack bonus +1.															PRETOTALAB:1	DESC:Your uncanny aim allows you to disable your opponents without harming them.								SOURCEPAGE:p.9	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on ranged combat maneuvers. When you attempt to perform a ranged combat maneuver, you can refrain from damaging the target at no penalty.
Volley Fire			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot																											PRETEXT:Point-Blank Shot.																						DESC:You have trained to work in ranks of archers to rain arrows down upon your foes.							SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:You gain a +1 bonus on ranged attack rolls for each ally with this feat who made a ranged attack since the end of your last turn against a target within 15 feet of your target, to a maximum of +4. These allies don't provide cover against your attacks.
Warning Shot		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot,Precise Shot,Weapon Focus																							PRETEXT:Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Weapon Focus, proficiency with the selected weapon.											DESC:An intentional near-miss demonstrates your frightening skill at range.									SOURCEPAGE:p.11	BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can make a ranged touch attack using a ranged weapon with which you have Weapon Focus. If successful, instead of dealing damage or applying any other effects of the attack, you may attempt an Intimidate check to demoralize the target as a free action. The target doesn't need to be within 30 feet, nor does it need to be able to see or hear you.
Weathered Warrior		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Endurance																												PRETEXT:Endurance.																							DESC:You have a steady hand in any weather.														SOURCEPAGE:p.15	BENEFIT:In areas of strong or severe wind (CRB p.439) or when affected by wind effects or spells that penalize ranged attacks, you take only half the ranged attack penalty. You can make ranged attacks in windstorm-level winds at a –4 penalty.
